Tragedy, on Tuesday, struck in Owerri, as a final year student of the  Imo State university, was crushed by a heavy duty truck while he was on his way for the school’s first semester examination. Eyewitnesses said that the student was killed by a truck with the number plate, EBONYI XD 520 AKL at about 7: 50am, at IMSU Junction, a few meters away from the campus where he was to sit for the examination. According to the source, the truck which was coming into town from the Okigwe – Owerri Expressway, had break failure and crushed the student who apparently jumped out of the tricycle he was travelling in. The corpse has since been evacuated by the police. Details later…